  "text": "The Firefox SpiderMonkey JavaScript parsing to bytecode compilation pipeline follows this architecture:\n\n**1. Parser Entry Point (js/src/frontend/Parser.h, js/src/frontend/Parser.cpp):**\nThe parser hierarchy consists of ParserBase (base class for all parsers), PerHandlerParser (behavior shared across parse-handling modes), GeneralParser (character-type and handler-aware parsing), and specialized Parser<ParseHandler, Unit> templates. The GeneralParser class contains the core parsing logic that reads tokens and creates the Abstract Syntax Tree (AST).\n\n**2. AST Node Types (js/src/frontend/ParseNode.h, js/src/jsast.tbl):**\nThe AST is defined through the ParseNode class hierarchy in ParseNode.h, with node kinds enumerated using the FOR_EACH_PARSE_NODE_KIND macro. Each node type (EmptyStmt, ExpressionStmt, CommaExpr, PropertyDefinition, etc.) maps to a corresponding ParseNode subclass (NullaryNode, UnaryNode, BinaryNode, ListNode, etc.). The jsast.tbl file provides a table of all AST node kinds with their names.\n\n**3. Bytecode Emitter (js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.h, js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.cpp):**\nThe BytecodeEmitter class receives the parsed AST and generates bytecode sequences and related stencil data. BytecodeEmitter walks the AST and emits JSOp instructions (defined in vm/Opcodes.h), managing scope information, variable bindings, and jump targets. The emitter generates both prologue code (variable instantiation) and main code sections.\n\n**4. Intermediate Representation - Stencil (js/src/frontend/Stencil.h, js/src/frontend/Stencil.cpp):**\nStencils are the intermediate representation produced by parsing and bytecode emission. ScriptStencil contains bytecode and metadata for each script/function. ExtensibleCompilationStencil holds mutable vectors during compilation; CompilationStencil is the immutable, reference-counted result. This decouples compilation from the GC heap, enabling caching and speculation.\n\n**5. JSScript Bytecode Output (js/src/vm/JSScript.h, js/src/vm/JSScript.cpp):**\nJSScript is the final runtime representation of compiled JavaScript. It contains the bytecode array, scope information, GC thing references (constants, functions, regexps), source notes (mapping bytecode to source), and metadata like flags and line numbers. JSScript::fullyInitialize creates the immutable script data from the stencil.\n\n**6. Compilation Driver (js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.h, js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp):**\nThe high-level compilation functions like CompileGlobalScriptToStencilImpl orchestrate the entire pipeline: they create a Parser, call parsing methods to generate the AST, instantiate a BytecodeEmitter, emit bytecode into stencils, and handle instantiation of JSScript objects on the GC heap.\n\n**Complete pipeline:** Source text → TokenStream → Parser → AST (ParseNode tree) → BytecodeEmitter → Stencil (CompilationStencil) → JSScript (on GC heap) → VM execution"
}

